HEADWORD: Peccability
<hw>Pec`ca*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or
quality of being peccable; liability to sin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The common <qex>peccability</qex> of mankind.</q> <rj><qau>Dr. H.
More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peccable</ent>⟦br⟧
